I am Lee Bang Won.
Episode 42

3
00:00:50,650 --> 00:00:52,850
Who are you?

4
00:00:52,850 --> 00:00:57,390
I am Ju Che (Zhu Di)!

5
00:00:58,450 --> 00:01:00,330
Ju Che (Zhu Di)...

6
00:01:00,330 --> 00:01:04,230
What did he say his name was?

7
00:01:05,340 --> 00:01:10,620
He said he's called Ju Che.

8
00:01:10,620 --> 00:01:13,670
Ju Che?
(Ju Che (Zhu Di): Later 3rd Ming Emperor Yeong Rak Emperor, also Yongle Emperor)

9
00:01:13,670 --> 00:01:16,450
Who the hell is Ju Che?

10
00:01:16,450 --> 00:01:21,890
He's the fourth son of Zhu Yuanzhang and was appointed king of Yuan areas.

11
00:01:40,730 --> 00:01:44,010
Your Highness, what's going on?

12
00:01:46,750 --> 00:01:51,110
This kid asked me if I wanted to die.

13
00:02:10,370 --> 00:02:12,720
Cut one of his arms first!

14
00:02:29,540 --> 00:02:33,700
Moo Hyul, no! Stop it! That person is the king.

15
00:02:33,700 --> 00:02:36,260
I don't know about that.

16
00:02:36,260 --> 00:02:41,240
King or not, if I stab him, the sword would still go in.

17
00:02:44,190 --> 00:02:50,420
Teacher Ha Ryun, please translate Moo Hyul's words.

18
00:02:50,420 --> 00:02:52,870
Why are you doing this, Your Highness?

19
00:02:52,870 --> 00:02:55,130
Translate it!

20
00:02:57,910 --> 00:02:59,830
I understood it.

21
00:03:02,050 --> 00:03:04,810
So you know our language.

22
00:03:06,330 --> 00:03:08,170
I do.

23
00:03:08,170 --> 00:03:13,170
Then, I will tell you myself.

24
00:03:15,570 --> 00:03:21,570
That ignorant guy who doesn't even know how to write his own name

25
00:03:21,570 --> 00:03:26,690
obviously doesn't know who the king is.

26
00:03:28,250 --> 00:03:32,450
If I tell him to cut you down, he will do so.

27
00:03:32,450 --> 00:03:40,790
Moo Hyul, count to ten in your head then you can cut him if you want.

28
00:03:43,450 --> 00:03:46,430
Yes, Your Highness.

29
00:03:52,440 --> 00:03:56,700
This guy is totally a crazy bastard.

30
00:04:34,430 --> 00:04:39,240
Because of you, all of us are going to die.

31
00:04:42,070 --> 00:04:43,930
Beat him up.

32
00:04:53,890 --> 00:04:58,710
Because he put a sword to my neck, that guy will die.

33
00:04:58,710 --> 00:05:00,330
Your Highness.

34
00:05:00,330 --> 00:05:03,810
Since he risked his life to protect his lord's life,

35
00:05:03,810 --> 00:05:07,140
I will return the corpse.

36
00:05:07,140 --> 00:05:11,140
We were not the first ones who were disrespectful.

37
00:05:12,250 --> 00:05:18,270
We are Joseon's envoy group who came to answer the emperor's summons.

38
00:05:18,270 --> 00:05:25,090
But you arrested us in Liaodong fortress without any explanation

39
00:05:25,090 --> 00:05:32,990
and Your Highness hid your identity and insulted us.

40
00:05:34,590 --> 00:05:36,850
His country

41
00:05:37,930 --> 00:05:43,190
and his master is in danger while being insulted,

42
00:05:43,190 --> 00:05:46,710
how can a bodyguard just stay still?

43
00:05:48,150 --> 00:05:50,050
That's right.

44
00:05:52,690 --> 00:05:55,850
Tell his family

45
00:05:55,850 --> 00:05:59,130
that he died a loyal death.

46
00:05:59,130 --> 00:06:02,010
He was a good subordinate for a barbarian.

47
00:06:48,370 --> 00:06:53,520
"Only the wise can deal with those who have more than they."

48
00:06:53,520 --> 00:06:58,230
"Only the kind-hearted can work with those who have less than they."

49
00:07:01,900 --> 00:07:09,440
Only a good person can serve a small country despite his great country."

50
00:07:09,440 --> 00:07:17,000
Only a wise person can take a small country and serve a great country.

51
00:07:19,300 --> 00:07:26,880
Therefore, the great country has to act with kindness and virtue

52
00:07:26,880 --> 00:07:31,000
so that the small country can serve with courtesy.

53
00:07:32,170 --> 00:07:38,170
Virtue and courtesy are exchangeable.

54
00:07:41,020 --> 00:07:48,890
But since you did not treat us with virtue,

55
00:07:49,840 --> 00:07:56,750
our rudeness was caused by you.

56
00:07:59,180 --> 00:08:06,710
Mencius. Book of King Yang Hye, third chapter of the last volume.

57
00:08:10,900 --> 00:08:16,390
I also like Mencius. There are some things to nitpick but he's an interesting person.

58
00:08:16,390 --> 00:08:18,430
How did you know our language?

59
00:08:18,430 --> 00:08:24,680
Manchurian, Mongolian, Timurid, Tartar, Goryeo language. I can speak them all.

60
00:08:24,680 --> 00:08:27,350
My Father is His Majesty the Emperor.

61
00:08:28,110 --> 00:08:31,310
Do you know how many of his royal concubines are Goryeo women?

62
00:08:33,670 --> 00:08:35,910
My nursemaid was also from Goryeo.

63
00:08:35,910 --> 00:08:38,390
It's not Goryeo anymore.

64
00:08:38,390 --> 00:08:40,870
It's Joseon, Your Highness.

65
00:08:46,050 --> 00:08:50,790
That's right. A new country was created, right?

66
00:08:50,790 --> 00:08:52,610
Your Highness,

67
00:08:55,290 --> 00:09:02,710
please spare my bodyguard's life.

68
00:09:04,880 --> 00:09:07,520
That man cannot live whatever he does.

69
00:09:09,460 --> 00:09:12,010
Since a sword was put on my neck,

70
00:09:12,010 --> 00:09:17,360
I will also kill all of my bodyguards. They have to take responsibility.

71
00:09:17,360 --> 00:09:22,000
So how would I be able to spare just his life?

72
00:09:26,170 --> 00:09:27,500
Whatever you say—

73
00:09:27,500 --> 00:09:32,490
Yes, that's right.

74
00:09:33,220 --> 00:09:36,600
You must kill all of them. Of course.

75
00:09:38,050 --> 00:09:43,430
Then, please let him die while fighting.

76
00:09:47,580 --> 00:09:51,100
Are you saying that you're confident?

77
00:09:51,100 --> 00:09:53,640
It's not because I'm confident.

78
00:09:54,630 --> 00:09:59,970
That man's dream as a warrior...

79
00:09:59,970 --> 00:10:03,710
He came to me with just that dream alone.

80
00:10:05,050 --> 00:10:10,870
Even if he dies, it shouldn't be like this.

81
00:10:11,930 --> 00:10:19,300
Let him die fighting as a warrior, Your Highness.

82
00:10:32,580 --> 00:10:34,680
This will be interesting.

83
00:10:43,130 --> 00:10:45,110
Moo Hyul...

84
00:10:52,640 --> 00:10:54,300
It's alright.

85
00:10:58,200 --> 00:11:00,680
You tried to protect me

86
00:11:02,730 --> 00:11:05,100
but I don't have the power to protect you.

87
00:11:07,790 --> 00:11:10,480
The only thing that I can do

88
00:11:10,480 --> 00:11:13,640
is give you an opportunity to fight.

89
00:11:13,640 --> 00:11:15,070
You mean...

90
00:11:17,060 --> 00:11:19,390
Staying alive is your part.

91
00:11:20,990 --> 00:11:22,850
That is all I need.

92
00:11:23,520 --> 00:11:26,060
That is all....

93
00:11:26,060 --> 00:11:28,130
Let's stay alive.

94
00:11:28,130 --> 00:11:30,160
I'll live

95
00:11:30,900 --> 00:11:32,530
only if you live.

96
00:11:45,900 --> 00:11:49,220
The 25th move of The Twin Dragons of the East. Moo Hyul.

97
00:11:49,220 --> 00:11:53,210
The 25th move that I developed while watching Bang Ji copying Cheok Sa Gwang

98
00:11:53,210 --> 00:11:55,620
You've practiced it a lot all this time.

99
00:11:55,620 --> 00:11:58,790
Although it's not that good to try it out in a real match

100
00:11:59,830 --> 00:12:02,780
I believe it's definitely going to work.

101
00:12:02,780 --> 00:12:04,680
Don't be afraid.

102
00:12:04,680 --> 00:12:06,590
I'm not afraid.

103
00:12:07,480 --> 00:12:09,700
Since I can fight

104
00:12:09,700 --> 00:12:11,670
I feel rather at peace.

105
00:12:11,670 --> 00:12:14,300
Right. That's right.

106
00:12:15,360 --> 00:12:17,340
Peace within tension.

107
00:12:17,340 --> 00:12:19,010
The best condition.

108
00:12:20,160 --> 00:12:23,450
You... You can beat anyone.

109
00:12:23,450 --> 00:12:26,400
You can do it. I believe in you.

110
00:12:26,400 --> 00:12:28,560
But, Teacher.

111
00:12:28,560 --> 00:12:30,120
Yes, what?

112
00:12:32,230 --> 00:12:34,930
If something goes wrong, my grandmother—

113
00:12:34,930 --> 00:12:36,340
No!

114
00:12:39,730 --> 00:12:42,360
I... I can't take responsibility.

115
00:12:43,450 --> 00:12:47,410
Stay alive and take responsibility yourself.

116
00:13:00,710 --> 00:13:03,930
Twin Dragons of the East!

117
00:13:03,930 --> 00:13:10,100
Twin Dragons of the East!

118
00:13:10,100 --> 00:13:12,630
Twin Dragons of the East!

119
00:13:12,630 --> 00:13:18,670
Twin Dragons of the East!

120
00:13:21,710 --> 00:13:23,910
Twin Dragons of the East!

121
00:13:23,910 --> 00:13:25,580
Moo Hyul.

122
00:13:25,580 --> 00:13:28,330
Don't be afraid. You can't be afraid.

123
00:13:28,330 --> 00:13:31,330
Don't be afraid.

124
00:13:32,220 --> 00:13:33,540
Take a deep breath.

125
00:13:33,540 --> 00:13:36,000
Think about a still lake.

126
00:13:36,000 --> 00:13:39,910
You are water. It's so calm and still.

127
00:13:39,910 --> 00:13:41,390
It's so calm and still.

128
00:13:41,390 --> 00:13:42,920
Teacher.

129
00:13:42,920 --> 00:13:44,720
It seems like you are more nervous than I am.

130
00:13:44,720 --> 00:13:46,150
Oh, right.

131
00:14:30,140 --> 00:14:31,840
Start!

132
00:14:49,860 --> 00:14:51,450
Moo Hyul! Dodge!

133
00:14:51,450 --> 00:14:53,340
Step one of the 25th move!

134
00:14:59,890 --> 00:15:01,450
Moo Hyul! Dodge!

135
00:15:18,660 --> 00:15:19,820
Don't rush! Dodge!

136
00:15:19,820 --> 00:15:22,500
Avoid and attack. Avoid and hit once!

137
00:16:40,860 --> 00:16:42,530
Stop!

138
00:16:43,900 --> 00:16:45,490
Stop!

139
00:16:58,540 --> 00:17:01,080
Moo Hyul, stop!

140
00:17:54,340 --> 00:17:56,200
It is your victory.

141
00:18:00,990 --> 00:18:02,910
Tell me your wish.

142
00:18:08,300 --> 00:18:10,950
Because of what I did today,

143
00:18:11,650 --> 00:18:13,880
I heard that

144
00:18:13,880 --> 00:18:16,870
your guards may die.

145
00:18:18,150 --> 00:18:20,200
Please spare

146
00:18:22,670 --> 00:18:24,200
their lives.

147
00:18:24,200 --> 00:18:25,500
Why?

148
00:18:36,070 --> 00:18:38,770
There's a connection

149
00:18:39,630 --> 00:18:41,850
among people who protect others.

150
00:18:43,730 --> 00:18:46,820
They will want to protect again

151
00:18:47,660 --> 00:18:49,340
and

152
00:18:50,680 --> 00:18:52,980
they will protect even better.

153
00:19:07,470 --> 00:19:09,920
This man is telling me to forgive you all.

154
00:19:12,690 --> 00:19:14,560
I will!

155
00:19:17,300 --> 00:19:21,350
The benevolence of the king is great!

156
00:20:02,860 --> 00:20:07,890
As even the 5th prince has such a talented guard,

157
00:20:08,500 --> 00:20:10,650
Joseon is indeed a dangerous country.

158
00:20:11,690 --> 00:20:15,830
And so, I can't let you pass.

159
00:20:15,830 --> 00:20:17,330
Go back.

160
00:20:17,330 --> 00:20:18,870
Your Majesty.

161
00:20:20,190 --> 00:20:23,810
I have never let one of your envoys pass.

162
00:20:23,810 --> 00:20:27,690
But we have received orders to come from the Emperor.

163
00:20:27,690 --> 00:20:29,660
That is your circumstance.

164
00:20:42,630 --> 00:20:45,240
Namgyeong: Ming's capital in the beginning

165
00:20:46,340 --> 00:20:48,150
Did you see it?

166
00:20:49,520 --> 00:20:51,890
The maps in the barracks.

167
00:20:53,130 --> 00:20:54,370
Maps?

168
00:20:54,370 --> 00:20:59,350
Ju Che (Zhu Di) is saying that there is a war brewing between Yeojin (Jurchen) and Joseon,

169
00:20:59,350 --> 00:21:02,790
and he even came all the way here to train soldiers.

170
00:21:02,790 --> 00:21:04,710
But...

171
00:21:04,710 --> 00:21:08,260
All of his maps are maps of the Central Plain.

172
00:21:09,770 --> 00:21:11,800
Do you know what they are?

173
00:21:12,520 --> 00:21:14,330
You do, right?

174
00:21:14,330 --> 00:21:18,640
In what state are Mainland's internal affairs right now?

175
00:21:19,470 --> 00:21:22,960
We have to pass. Let's make a bet.

176
00:21:23,900 --> 00:21:26,100
Why do you keep

177
00:21:27,850 --> 00:21:31,880
on creating a tense relationship with Joseon?

178
00:21:35,120 --> 00:21:36,700
What?

179
00:21:36,700 --> 00:21:38,820
Your Highness

180
00:21:40,810 --> 00:21:44,330
fabricated a case that never existed

181
00:21:45,640 --> 00:21:47,850
and kept nitpicking at it.

182
00:21:47,850 --> 00:21:51,530
You sent a fake report to the emperor.

183
00:21:51,530 --> 00:21:52,840
You bastard!

184
00:21:54,590 --> 00:21:57,560
How dare you speak such imprecations!

185
00:21:59,230 --> 00:22:01,130
Why do you think

186
00:22:01,700 --> 00:22:04,160
that I lied about something like that?

187
00:22:04,990 --> 00:22:06,990
Because you want to steal

188
00:22:08,250 --> 00:22:10,900
the throne from your nephew.

189
00:22:17,130 --> 00:22:19,140
Continue.

190
00:22:19,140 --> 00:22:21,480
The next in throne will be

191
00:22:21,480 --> 00:22:25,150
the emperor's eldest grandson, your young nephew.

192
00:22:26,130 --> 00:22:29,440
His Majesty the Emperor will obviously

193
00:22:29,440 --> 00:22:33,270
be anxious of Your Highness' power.

194
00:22:34,000 --> 00:22:35,540
So...

195
00:22:36,400 --> 00:22:39,300
Didn't you do it

196
00:22:40,300 --> 00:22:42,850
because you were scared of the emperor's suspicions?

197
00:22:42,850 --> 00:22:45,400
Just what are you saying?

198
00:22:55,370 --> 00:23:00,820
Because of the unstable political tension between Joseon and Yeojin (Jurchen), you have no interest in the imperial throne.

199
00:23:00,820 --> 00:23:03,610
Even just protecting this place is too much.

200
00:23:03,610 --> 00:23:06,550
Aren't you trying to present yourself this way to the emperor?

201
00:23:07,250 --> 00:23:08,650
So?

202
00:23:08,650 --> 00:23:10,820
Your Highness

203
00:23:11,530 --> 00:23:14,940
reported to the emperor that Joseon is dangerous.

204
00:23:14,940 --> 00:23:17,840
His Majesty the Emperor

205
00:23:17,840 --> 00:23:21,070
will be coming up with an uncompromising policy for Joseon.

206
00:23:21,070 --> 00:23:23,220
The result of that

207
00:23:24,430 --> 00:23:26,310
can really be war.

208
00:23:26,310 --> 00:23:28,350
Is that what you want?

209
00:23:30,960 --> 00:23:33,900
A cornered mouse

210
00:23:33,900 --> 00:23:36,720
can do nothing but bite the cat.

211
00:23:36,720 --> 00:23:38,970
But that is not

212
00:23:39,560 --> 00:23:41,450
what you wanted, right?

213
00:23:42,630 --> 00:23:44,860
Who says that I don't want that?

214
00:23:44,860 --> 00:23:46,040
Then,

215
00:23:48,430 --> 00:23:52,930
in this headquarters that was made for defense against Joseon and Yeojin (Jurchen),

216
00:23:53,990 --> 00:23:57,440
why is it that there are only maps of the central plain?

217
00:24:00,470 --> 00:24:03,460
Isn't it that your great ambition

218
00:24:03,460 --> 00:24:06,300
is pointed towards Namgyeong (Nanjing) in the central plain?

219
00:24:13,150 --> 00:24:17,110
Namgyeong (Nanjing): Ming's capital in the beginning

220
00:24:17,110 --> 00:24:19,030
What is it that you want to say?

221
00:24:19,030 --> 00:24:22,340
On the day that you head towards the central plain,

222
00:24:23,110 --> 00:24:25,690
you probably don't want a hostile relationship with Joseon

223
00:24:25,690 --> 00:24:28,850
to be an obstacle.

224
00:24:30,490 --> 00:24:33,170
The enemy, with no path for retreat,

225
00:24:33,170 --> 00:24:35,750
has no choice but to be desperate.

226
00:24:36,740 --> 00:24:38,980
In military tactics,

227
00:24:38,980 --> 00:24:42,340
it is said to fight the enemy only after giving them a path to retreat.

228
00:24:42,340 --> 00:24:45,200
So in order to make sure Joseon doesn't think of starting a war,

229
00:24:46,000 --> 00:24:48,290
create a way out.

230
00:24:48,290 --> 00:24:49,980
Is that it?

231
00:24:49,980 --> 00:24:52,740
Yes. That's right.

232
00:24:53,960 --> 00:24:59,420
So that the hardliners in Joseon who are in favor of a war do not gain power,

233
00:25:00,230 --> 00:25:05,040
I'm telling you that you should take hold of a good hand.

234
00:25:05,040 --> 00:25:06,980
A good hand?

235
00:25:06,980 --> 00:25:08,520
It's

236
00:25:09,410 --> 00:25:13,430
me. I, Lee Bang Won.

237
00:25:16,090 --> 00:25:19,820
To make sure that Joseon doesn't fight back in desperation,

238
00:25:19,820 --> 00:25:22,070
through me

239
00:25:22,070 --> 00:25:25,020
please open a way out.

240
00:25:28,310 --> 00:25:30,510
Please let us

241
00:25:30,510 --> 00:25:32,950
pass through Liaodong.

242
00:25:37,630 --> 00:25:39,490
You are really

243
00:25:40,360 --> 00:25:42,260
wise

244
00:25:43,120 --> 00:25:44,820
and bold.

245
00:25:46,370 --> 00:25:48,090
But

246
00:25:49,080 --> 00:25:51,860
you're also arrogant and foolish!

247
00:25:53,510 --> 00:25:57,640
Don't you know that you could die because of what you said?

248
00:26:00,290 --> 00:26:02,400
You can also be found dead

249
00:26:03,960 --> 00:26:07,280
all of a sudden tomorrow.

250
00:26:07,280 --> 00:26:08,970
I

251
00:26:10,020 --> 00:26:12,860
bet I won't be.

252
00:26:20,050 --> 00:26:21,920
Today, you

253
00:26:23,760 --> 00:26:25,530
either die

254
00:26:27,020 --> 00:26:28,690
or live.

255
00:26:38,690 --> 00:26:40,390
What happened?

256
00:26:45,500 --> 00:26:47,350
It seems that we'll either die...

257
00:26:47,350 --> 00:26:48,530
Pardon?

258
00:26:49,200 --> 00:26:51,660
or pass through Liaodong.

259
00:26:57,860 --> 00:27:00,400
That is true.

260
00:27:01,810 --> 00:27:05,120
What a smart person I'm serving...

261
00:27:23,780 --> 00:27:27,530
Tell His Highness that I want to see him.

262
00:27:31,340 --> 00:27:32,840
Untie him.

263
00:27:37,810 --> 00:27:39,420
You must be surprised.

264
00:27:42,390 --> 00:27:45,160
There's still something shocking left though.

265
00:27:47,130 --> 00:27:48,660
Come in.

266
00:28:04,940 --> 00:28:07,530
I heard that you know each other.

267
00:28:07,530 --> 00:28:12,880
Your Highness, it's amazing that we meet here.

268
00:28:15,130 --> 00:28:17,030
How could you...

269
00:28:17,030 --> 00:28:22,130
As I was pondering whether I should kill you or make you a way out,

270
00:28:22,130 --> 00:28:24,560
I found out a lot about you.

271
00:28:28,230 --> 00:28:31,130
She's the leader of a group that's also famous in the Mainland.

